\usepackage{amssymb}
\usepackage{amsbsy}
\usepackage{upgreek}
\usepackage{mathrsfs}
\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
\begin{document}
}{}$G_{\text{pre}}$\end{document}, results in the fact that a log-normal distribution provides a better fit.

Given the strong dependence of the fitting procedure on the choice for \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
