In many situations, a population has already been vaccinated against an infectious disease before the disease is introduced, with the goal of preventing the disease from ever becoming endemic in the population. In this context, it is reasonable to treat the vaccinated sub-population as static in modelling the spread of disease. For a given vaccination strategy, we define the critical vaccination threshold \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\usepackage{wasysym}
\usepackage{amsfonts}
