\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
\begin{document}
}{}$N$\end{document} for all \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\usepackage{wasysym}
\usepackage{amsfonts}
\usepackage{amssymb}
\usepackage{amsbsy}
\usepackage{upgreek}
\usepackage{mathrsfs}
\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
\begin{document}
}{}$t$\end{document} after the disease is introduced in a finite number of nodes. (In this case, in the limit of a large population size, only a negligible fraction of the population will ever be infected.) If the vaccinated fraction of the population exceeds the critical threshold, then herd immunity is immediately achieved at \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\usepackage{wasysym}
