}{}$i(t) \equiv 0$\end{document}. Intuitively, the critical threshold describes the level of vaccination required to prevent the disease from ever becoming established at all, and not the level required to suppress an existing epidemic (which would depend on \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\usepackage{wasysym}
\usepackage{amsfonts}
\usepackage{amssymb}
